{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Extend each G j to a frame G ′ j for L(Φ, {i, ▷, ◁, ⊊, +}) such that the accessibility relations for i, ▷, ◁, and ⊊ are empty in G ′ j.",
    "Then it is easy to see that each G ′ j is still a full possibility frame, and the polymodal logics of the G ′ j are still pairwise distinct.",
    "Finally, consider the continuum-sized set {F G ′ j } j∈J where F G ′ j is the disjoint union of F and G ′ j as in Definition 5.56.",
    "We claim that (i) the logic of each F G ′ j is Kripke-frame incomplete and (ii) the logics of the F G ′ j are pairwise distinct.",
    "For (i), for our chosen φ and ψ above, we showed that (Split) is valid over F, and (Split) is valid over G ′ j since the accessibility relation for i is empty in G ′ j, so (Split) is valid over F G ′ j by Proposition 5.57."
